This blonde beauty, <b>Mitzi Strother</b>, went on to compete as Miss Miami in the 1941 Miss America Pageant in Atlantic City.  As part of a pageant questionnaire, she revealed she could trace her ancestry to Davy Crockett, among others.  (Miss California won the 1941 Miss America title.)

She married Lieut. Corbin Dekalb Stevens in 1942. [<a href="http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2206&amp;dat=19420703&amp;id=dQYtAAAAIBAJ&amp;sjid=Z9QFAAAAIBAJ&amp;pg=2725,601536" rel="nofollow">1</a>] <a href="http://fultonhistory.com/Newspaper4/Amsterdam NY Daily Democrat and Recorder/Amsterdam NY Daily Democrat and Recorder 1941 Aug-Nov Grayscale/Amsterdam NY Daily Democrat and Recorder 1941 Aug-Nov Grayscale - 0149.pdf" rel="nofollow">[2]</a> [<a href="http://www.missamerica.org/our-miss-americas/1940/1941.aspx" rel="nofollow">3</a>]
